---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import Container from "@/components/container.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Founder Story"
  description="Co-founder of Startup Village, Pupilfirst, and The Second Design. 12+ years building education infrastructure, partnering with governments and tech giants, and learning what actually helps students succeed."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-white border-b border-slate-200">
    <Container>
      <div class="max-w-6xl py-20">
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-5 gap-12 items-start">
          <!-- Photo -->
          <div class="md:col-span-2">
            <div class="aspect-square bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-100 to-indigo-100 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center text-6xl font-bold text-blue-600">
              G
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-3 text-center">
              Photo: At Facebook HQ, Mountain View (2017)
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Bio -->
          <div class="md:col-span-3">
            <h1 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">
              Gautam
            </h1>
            <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
              Founder, EduMyna
            </p>
            <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              I've spent 12 years building education infrastructure at scale—from
              India's first PPP incubator to university-integrated programs to open-source
              learning management systems.
            </p>
            <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
              I've supported 500+ startups, partnered with Facebook, Apple, and 4 state
              governments, and learned what actually works when you're trying to help
              students succeed at scale.
            </p>

            <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
              <a
                href="/contact"
                class="px-6 py-3 bg-blue-600 text-white font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-700 transition"
              >
                Get in Touch
              </a>
              <a
                href="/story"
                class="px-6 py-3 bg-slate-100 text-slate-700 font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-slate-200 transition"
              >
                Read the Full Story
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>

  <Container>

    <!-- Quick Stats -->
    <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto my-20">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-8">
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-blue-600">12+</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-slate-600 mt-1">Years in Education</div>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-blue-600">500+</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-slate-600 mt-1">Startups Supported</div>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-blue-600">3,139</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-slate-600 mt-1">Jobs Created</div>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-blue-600">₹45Cr</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-slate-600 mt-1">Funding Raised by Alumni</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- What I Do -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto my-32">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-8">What I Do</h2>
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          I build education infrastructure that works at scale. Not prototypes. Not pilots.
          Systems that support thousands of students, integrate with universities, work
          with government policies, and actually improve outcomes.
        </p>
        <p>
          My approach combines <strong>technology</strong> (building platforms that scale),
          <strong>pedagogy</strong> (understanding what actually helps students learn), and
          <strong>operations</strong> (running programs that governments and universities
          will actually deploy).
        </p>
        <p>
          EduMyna is where all these learnings converge—a platform and program suite
          designed to take transformative education to millions.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Experience -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto my-32">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-12">Experience & Track Record</h2>

      <div class="space-y-8">

        <!-- EduMyna -->
        <div class="border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-6 bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-l-blue-600">
          <div class="flex justify-between items-start mb-3">
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Founder</h3>
              <p class="text-slate-600">EduMyna</p>
            </div>
            <span class="text-sm text-slate-500">2024 - Present</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Building open-source education infrastructure and RealWorldReady programs to help
            students develop agency, systems thinking, and career navigation skills. Raising
            funding to scale to millions of students through platform + programs model.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- The Second Design -->
        <div class="border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-6">
          <div class="flex justify-between items-start mb-3">
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Co-Founder</h3>
              <p class="text-slate-600">The Second Design (formerly HowToCBC)</p>
            </div>
            <span class="text-sm text-slate-500">2022 - Present</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Education design studio working with businesses, colleges, and nonprofits.
            Developed RealWorldReady program (63% rated 10/10). Selected to Maven Accelerator
            (top 75 from 2000+ applicants). Clients include McDonald's, IMG Academy, Glovo.
          </p>
          <div class="text-xs text-slate-600">
            <strong>Partner:</strong> Dr. Aruna Krishnamoorthy (former Harvard lecturer, astrophysicist)
          </div>
          <div class="mt-3 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-teal-100 text-teal-700 rounded text-xs">1,500+ learners</span>
            <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-teal-100 text-teal-700 rounded text-xs">100+ sessions</span>
            <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-teal-100 text-teal-700 rounded text-xs">Maven Accelerator</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Pupilfirst -->
        <div class="border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-6">
          <div class="flex justify-between items-start mb-3">
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Co-Founder</h3>
              <p class="text-slate-600">Pupilfirst (evolved from SV.CO)</p>
            </div>
            <span class="text-sm text-slate-500">2018 - Present</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Built education platform infrastructure comparable to Teachable.com ($100M+ valuation).
            Open-sourced core framework. Deployed across multiple universities for credit-integrated
            courses. Created rich curriculum system, admin interface, and coach dashboards.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-3 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 rounded text-xs">Open Source LMS</span>
            <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 rounded text-xs">ReasonML/React</span>
            <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 rounded text-xs">University Deployments</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- SV.CO -->
        <div class="border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-6">
          <div class="flex justify-between items-start mb-3">
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Co-Founder</h3>
              <p class="text-slate-600">SV.CO (digital transformation of Startup Village)</p>
            </div>
            <span class="text-sm text-slate-500">2015 - 2018</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Led pivot from physical to digital education platform. Built online startup school
            programs (Fintech, SaaS). Ran Silicon Valley cohort trips. Experimented with
            subscription models, university integration (Apple iOS @ Manipal), and job placement
            (Hackkar). Partnered with Facebook (VR program), Freshworks (SaaS program).
          </p>
          <div class="mt-3 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-700 rounded text-xs">3 Cohorts</span>
            <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-700 rounded text-xs">Silicon Valley Trips</span>
            <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-700 rounded text-xs">Facebook Partnership</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Startup Village -->
        <div class="border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-6">
          <div class="flex justify-between items-start mb-3">
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Co-Founder</h3>
              <p class="text-slate-600">Startup Village (India's first PPP incubator)</p>
            </div>
            <span class="text-sm text-slate-500">2012 - 2015</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Built and operated India's first Public-Private-Partnership technology incubator
            in partnership with Government of India and Kerala. Exceeded all commitments:
            supported 500 startups (promised 48), created 3,139 jobs, enabled ₹45Cr in funding.
            Ran massive programs: 10,000 Raspberry Pis distributed, Startup Boxes (MacBooks +
            iPads), SV Square (Silicon Valley trips), MIT Fab Labs partnership.
          </p>
          <div class="text-xs text-slate-600 mb-3">
            <strong>ROI:</strong> For every ₹1 by govt, ₹9.68 invested into startups by investors
            | For every ₹15,309 by govt, 1 job created
          </div>
          <div class="mt-3 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-700 rounded text-xs">500 Startups</span>
            <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-700 rounded text-xs">₹14.6Cr Total Investment</span>
            <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-700 rounded text-xs">MIT Partnership</span>
            <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-700 rounded text-xs">4 State Govts</span>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Key Partnerships -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto my-32">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-8">Strategic Partnerships</h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-12 leading-relaxed">
        Over 12 years, I've collaborated with governments, tech giants, and universities
        to build and deploy education programs at scale.
      </p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">

        <!-- Tech Companies -->
        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-blue-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M21 13.255A23.931 23.931 0 0112 15c-3.183 0-6.22-.62-9-1.745M16 6V4a2 2 0 00-2-2h-4a2 2 0 00-2 2v2m4 6h.01M5 20h14a2 2 0 002-2V8a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2z" />
            </svg>
            Technology Companies
          </h3>
          <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-slate-700">
            <div>
              <strong>Facebook (Meta)</strong>
              <p class="text-slate-600">School of Innovation VR program (fully funded enterprise partnership)</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <strong>Apple</strong>
              <p class="text-slate-600">iOS development programs integrated with Manipal University</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <strong>Freshworks</strong>
              <p class="text-slate-600">Alpha SaaS development school partnership</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <strong>Maven</strong>
              <p class="text-slate-600">Accelerator program (top 75 from 2000+ global applicants)</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Governments -->
        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-blue-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 21V5a2 2 0 00-2-2H7a2 2 0 00-2 2v16m14 0h2m-2 0h-5m-9 0H3m2 0h5M9 7h1m-1 4h1m4-4h1m-1 4h1m-5 10v-5a1 1 0 011-1h2a1 1 0 011 1v5m-4 0h4" />
            </svg>
            Government Partnerships
          </h3>
          <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-slate-700">
            <div>
              <strong>Government of India</strong>
              <p class="text-slate-600">NSTEDB partnership for PPP incubator (₹4.8Cr funding)</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <strong>Government of Kerala</strong>
              <p class="text-slate-600">Kerala Startup Mission, infrastructure support (₹1.65Cr)</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <strong>Government of Andhra Pradesh</strong>
              <p class="text-slate-600">Vizag campus operations (₹2.4Cr investment)</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <strong>Government of Rajasthan</strong>
              <p class="text-slate-600">Startup exposure programs (Jan-June 2018)</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <strong>Government of Gujarat</strong>
              <p class="text-slate-600">Silicon Valley visit programs for student startups</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Universities -->
        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-blue-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6.253v13m0-13C10.832 5.477 9.246 5 7.5 5S4.168 5.477 3 6.253v13C4.168 18.477 5.754 18 7.5 18s3.332.477 4.5 1.253m0-13C13.168 5.477 14.754 5 16.5 5c1.747 0 3.332.477 4.5 1.253v13C19.832 18.477 18.247 18 16.5 18c-1.746 0-3.332.477-4.5 1.253" />
            </svg>
            Academic Institutions
          </h3>
          <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-slate-700">
            <div>
              <strong>MIT (Massachusetts Institute of Technology)</strong>
              <p class="text-slate-600">Fab Labs partnership for hardware startup support</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <strong>Manipal University (MIT Manipal)</strong>
              <p class="text-slate-600">First university-integrated course (Apple iOS development)</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <strong>Sastra University</strong>
              <p class="text-slate-600">VR and SaaS development credit-integrated programs</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <strong>Gujarat Technological University (GTU)</strong>
              <p class="text-slate-600">First executed university agreement for entrepreneurship minors</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <strong>GLS University</strong>
              <p class="text-slate-600">Partnership for startup education programs</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Other -->
        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-blue-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0M15 7a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm6 3a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0zM7 10a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0z" />
            </svg>
            Clients & Collaborations
          </h3>
          <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-slate-700">
            <div>
              <strong>McDonald's</strong>
              <p class="text-slate-600">Learning experience design (The Second Design)</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <strong>IMG Academy</strong>
              <p class="text-slate-600">Education program design</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <strong>Glovo</strong>
              <p class="text-slate-600">Learning experience design</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <strong>FOSS United</strong>
              <p class="text-slate-600">Open-source community programs</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <strong>Indian Ed-tech Unicorn</strong>
              <p class="text-slate-600">Strategic partnership (The Second Design era)</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Philosophy -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto my-32 bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-50 to-blue-50 rounded-2xl p-12 border border-slate-200">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-8">My Approach to Education</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">1. Mission Over Metrics</h3>
          <p class="text-sm">
            The mission has never changed: help others enable themselves. What changed is
            understanding how—from entrepreneurship to skills to transformative learning experiences.
            Revenue is necessary for sustainability, but it's never been the primary goal.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">2. Respond to Reality, Not Theory</h3>
          <p class="text-sm">
            Every major pivot came from listening to what worked. Students showed strongest
            signal, so we focused on students. Skills mattered more than startup advice, so
            we pivoted to skills. The market told us what it needed; we iterated.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">3. Systems Thinking, Not Silver Bullets</h3>
          <p class="text-sm">
            Education is a complex system—teachers, institutions, policy, incentives, culture.
            No single company can fix it alone. Change requires patience, collaboration across
            stakeholders, and infrastructure that others can build on (hence open-source).
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">4. Scale + Quality, Not One or the Other</h3>
          <p class="text-sm">
            Cheap education at scale often sacrifices quality. Expensive education is exclusionary.
            The challenge is cracking the equation—high quality, low cost, massive scale. That's
            what EduMyna is designed to solve.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">5. Open Source as Trust Infrastructure</h3>
          <p class="text-sm">
            Closed platforms create lock-in. Open-source creates trust. When universities and
            governments can inspect, modify, and self-host the platform, they'll actually deploy
            it. Transparency over control.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 p-6 bg-white rounded-xl border-2 border-blue-200">
        <p class="text-lg italic text-slate-800">
          "I think it's relatively easier to build businesses whose primary function is to
          make money. What is harder is to build companies that do the kind of work that
          nourishes the soul. It's a challenge we've attempted and we've been rather successful at it."
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 mt-3">
          — From the Evolution of Startup Village documentation
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Skills & Expertise -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto my-32">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-12">Skills & Expertise</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Education Platform Building</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-blue-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>LMS architecture & deployment</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-blue-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Curriculum design systems</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-blue-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Open-source platform strategy</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-blue-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Multi-tenant SaaS infrastructure</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Program Design & Operations</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-blue-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Cohort-based learning design</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-blue-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>University integration models</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-blue-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Facilitator training & guides</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-blue-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Feedback loops & iteration</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Strategic Partnerships</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-blue-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Government collaboration (4 states)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-blue-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Corporate partnerships (FB, Apple)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-blue-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>University agreements & integration</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-blue-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>PPP model structuring</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Why I'm Building EduMyna -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto my-32">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-8">Why I'm Building EduMyna</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          After 12 years, I've learned what works and what doesn't. I've built the infrastructure
          (Pupilfirst LMS). I've tested the pedagogy (RealWorldReady outcomes). I've proven I
          can partner with governments and tech giants. I know how to navigate pivots.
        </p>
        <p>
          But there's still 200 million young Indians who need better education. The system is
          still broken—attendance policies that don't make sense, theoretical content disconnected
          from careers, no real support for developing agency and initiative.
        </p>
        <p>
          EduMyna is my attempt to take everything I've learned and build the platform + programs
          that can actually reach them. Fork the LMS, open-source it, let universities self-host.
          Run RealWorldReady through The Second Design. Build the tech products that make it scale.
          Work with governments on policy. Get it to millions.
        </p>
        <p class="font-medium text-lg text-slate-900">
          I didn't start this journey 12 years ago. I'm continuing it. And I believe EduMyna
          is how we finally crack the equation.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto my-32 text-center">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-600 to-indigo-600 rounded-2xl p-12 text-white">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">
          Let's Talk
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg mb-8 opacity-90">
          If you're an investor, potential partner, or someone who believes education can be
          better, I'd love to connect. Let's build the infrastructure that helps millions of
          students succeed.
